4.01	Nuala_O'Loan	Nuala O'Loan	Nuala Patricia O'Loan, Baroness O'Loan, DBE (born 20 December 1951) is a noted public figure in Northern Ireland. She was the first Police Ombudsman in between 1999 and 2007. In July 2009, it was announced that she was to be appointed to the House of Lords. Consequently, she was raised to the peerage as Baroness O'Loan, of Kirkinriola in the County of Antrim on 11 September 2009. In December 2010, National University of Ireland, Maynooth appointed her as Chairman of its Governing Authority.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7d/Baroness_Nuala_O%27Loan.jpg/220px-Baroness_Nuala_O%27Loan.jpg
